gomodel:SYNGO_4525  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 4 indicates that OGT regulates the number but not the size of mature synaptic contacts as determined by counting number and puncta size of pre- (VGLUT) and postsynaptic (PSD-95) markers.\nFig. 5 shows that there are fewer and more immature spines of OGT KO neurons as assessed by the analysis of spines of GFP-expressing neurons.\n\n15/02/2021 Dnyanada: The paper demonstrates a reduction in the number of mature synapses as well as in the morphologically mature spines in OGT KO neurons. Figure 2 and 3 also demonstrate a reduction in the surface expression of GluR2 and GluR3 AMPAR subunits in OGT KO neurons. As the paper does not causally (and chronologically) link these two effects, a separate annotation for the term \"regulation of neurotransmitter receptor localisation to postsynaptic specialisation membrane\" was made (SynGO ID: 4521).. Experimental description: We developed a mouse model where OGT was deleted\ngenetically from mature brain neurons in vivo... (p. 1685) (cKO: PMID 26989246)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2021-02-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4525" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

